commit.message:
src/video.c: use %ld to print longs

ncurses-6.3 added printf()-stype attribute annotations for gcc-like
compilers that can now detect argument mismatches:

    video.c:114:26: error: format '%d' expects argument of type 'int',
      but argument 3 has type 'long unsigned int' [-Werror=format=]
      114 |                 printw(_("Viewing line %d/%d, 100%%"), lines, lines);
          |                          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

src/utils.c: suppres unused parameter warning

    utils.c:372:62: error: unused parameter 'completions' [-Werror=unused-parameter]
      372 | getstring_with_completion(char *prompt, const char * const * completions)
          |                                         ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^~~~~~~~~~~
workaround false positie in gcc-10 stringop-overflow checks
add more travis test targets
fix use of global variabel
update xcode images for travis builds

Fix typos in function key names

There were typos in the F9 and F10 key names, causing custom key binding not to work for those keys.
Spotted and fixed by Henning <xaoxx@t-online.de>

Fix type mismatch when allocating the inodes array

This fixes heap-based buffer overflow on systems that have ino_t wider
than a pointer.
